race.comment: Tricky. SIR TUA (8) impressed, missing a whisker at Kembla Grange first up, when expected to need it. Has the inside gate and will be tough to beat this grade with the extra fitness. ONOMA (7) debuts for a sharp Sydney barn and has been well educated. Won both his most recent trials at Warwick Farm, and despite the awkward gate, is likely to feature. The race-day betting will be key with him. CAMILLA (12) keeps finding one better, and she was heavily-backed beaten a whisker at Goulburn last time. Has the blinkers on for the first time, and they may do the trick. SOLAR ORBIT (3) resumes, and he showed enough on debut to consider. Will be naturally improved, and the in-form Boudvillain will give him every chance from a soft barrier. WHACK ATTACK (15) resumes for a leading juvenile barn. Didn't do a lot on debut as expected, but returns gelded and with the blinkers on for the first time. Has trialled well enough at Randwick, and the late betting will be key.
